
[1]perlexity

   PERLEX'ITY, n. Intricacy; entanglement. The jury were embarrassed by
   the perplexity of the case.

   1. Embarrassment of mind; disturbance from doubt, confusion, difficulty
   or anxiety.

   Perplexity not suffering them to be idle, they think and do, as it
   were, in a frenzy.
